    <refsection id="Description_CMRC_ElastoBacklash">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            This block is a backlash connected in series to linear spring and damper (backlash is modeled with elasticity).
            The torque <latex>\tau\:</latex> is computed:
        </para>
        <para>
            <Itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        If position is greater than half of backlash, then
                        <latex>
                            \begin{eqnarray}
                            \tau = c * (phi\_rel-phi\_rel0 - backlash) + d * \omega_{rel}
                            \end{eqnarray}
                        </latex>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        If position is lower than half of backlash, then
                        <latex>
                            \begin{eqnarray}
                            \tau = c * (phi\_rel-phi\_rel0 + backlash) + d * \omega_{rel}
                            \end{eqnarray}
                        </latex>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </Itemizedlist>
        </para>
        <para>
            with phi_rel the combined angle and <latex> \omega_{rel}\: </latex> the angular velocity in rad/s.
        </para>
        <para>
            Note that, if backlash is lower than <latex>2^{-10}\:</latex> rad, the system is reduced to a spring and a damper in parallel.
        </para>
    </refsection>
